<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/205549-should-these-be-read-in-order">Should these be read in order?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_205549'><a id="like_count_community_question_205549" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/205549?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">4 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F634407.Knots_and_Crosses">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/205549-should-these-be-read-in-order">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/205549-should-these-be-read-in-order">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/45407980-gemma"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1451396687i/45407980._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/45407980-gemma">Gemma</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Absolutely. I&apos;m about to start re-reading again (for the fifth or sixth time). Although the individual mysteries technically stand alone, there are se<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Absolutely. I'm about to start re-reading again (for the fifth or sixth time). Although the individual mysteries technically stand alone, there are several key players in the Edinburgh 'crime world' whose presence becomes increasingly threatening throughout the series. You won't really get a sense of the Rebus world unless you read them in order, at least the first few and the last few. The ones in the middle, it probably doesn't matter as much.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
