        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3266097708" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4084089034225312731"><b>Inspector Rebus mystery No. 1</b>: I&apos;d been toying with Rankin&apos;s other crime fiction work, but then it was time to read the real thing. The first Rebus novel. A captivating and at times consuming tale; there&apos;s a serial killer of young girls; and Rebus&apos; brother involved in drugs, and Rebus himself without a clue. Claustrophobic at times, stuck in the greasy, dark and cold world of Rebus, but has there ever been a more realistic portrayal of a man getting on, doing what he likes, the way he likes, usi</span>
  <span id="freeText4084089034225312731" style="display:none"><b>Inspector Rebus mystery No. 1</b>: I'd been toying with Rankin's other crime fiction work, but then it was time to read the real thing. The first Rebus novel. A captivating and at times consuming tale; there's a serial killer of young girls; and Rebus' brother involved in drugs, and Rebus himself without a clue. Claustrophobic at times, stuck in the greasy, dark and cold world of Rebus, but has there ever been a more realistic portrayal of a man getting on, doing what he likes, the way he likes, using all his past experience and skills as his steer, and not necessarily succeeding? 7 out of 12.<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1616071995i/31032538._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
