    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1639227162" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1639227162" />
    <a title="Susan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9365612-susan"><img alt="Susan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1395429381p2/9365612.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1639227162?book_show_action=true">May 15, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Susan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Susan" href="/user/show/9365612-susan">Susan</a>
      </span>

          added it


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/23209197-knots-and-crosses">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1639227162" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17502490781116791180">I&apos;ve seen Ian Rankin books all over airports, bookstores, libraries, best seller lists since I was first out of college and have never picked one up. Probably for the same reason I never picked up a Lawrence Block book. Big mistake, but now I have many more in the Detective John Rebus series left to read. I like Rankin&apos;s style, very moody and somewhat dark, although other reviews I&apos;ve read says he lightens up quite a bit in later novels. Considering this series is still going strong almost 30 ye</span>
  <span id="freeText17502490781116791180" style="display:none">I've seen Ian Rankin books all over airports, bookstores, libraries, best seller lists since I was first out of college and have never picked one up. Probably for the same reason I never picked up a Lawrence Block book. Big mistake, but now I have many more in the Detective John Rebus series left to read. I like Rankin's style, very moody and somewhat dark, although other reviews I've read says he lightens up quite a bit in later novels. Considering this series is still going strong almost 30 years in, it makes sense. If poor Rebus got any more depressed than he was here I'd be worried. For a tough guy, he spends a lot of this book in tears. I hope he's turned the corner in the book two! Will definitely be reading more of Mr. Rankin soon.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17502490781116791180" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1639227162">
